<font color="#FF0000">CHILDREN OF VN VETS</font><br>
<tt>Tue Jul  1 13:58:26 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
I am 31 years old and my father is a decorated Viet Nam Vet.  I have been a witness  - and unintended victim - of the demons that haunt him still.  I see the pain on his face when he finds the courage to tell me even a little bit about the horrors he witnessed (and participated in) there.  My love and sadness for him goes very deep and I have always respected his need for privacy - and for protection from having to recount those experiences.However, I am at a loss.  I need to understand what happened to him there, yet I am afraid to ask him directly.  He will tell me when he is ready.  But in the mean time, I am in a lot of pain and I need to put all the pieces back together in hopes that I can continue to support him and be a positive force in his life. I would like to start a dialogue, public or private, with other adult children of Viet Nam Vets.   Please contact me if you are interested or would like to share experiences.
